    "summary": "+1 Steve, focus management correctly deferred",
    "content": "+1 on your observations, Steve. The empty state messaging and accessible labels are good.\n\nOn your point #4 (focus after delete): I noticed that Luca mentioned a deferred item was recorded for \"focus management after HTMX delete for contexts.\" So this was identified and correctly deferred rather than ignored. That is the right process -- non-blocking a11y concerns go to `docs/deferred-items.md` and get reviewed at retros.\n\nOn point #5 (Cancel reloading the full page): Carson made the same observation. It is a minor inefficiency but works correctly. A dedicated fragment endpoint would be cleaner, and that could be addressed when we revisit contexts in a future step.\n\nNo additional concerns from my side on UX. The contexts management page is straightforward and does not make users think -- which is the goal."
